The sum of N10million has been earmarked by the Bauchi State Government for fumigation in order to guard against the spread of COVID-19 in the state.  The disclosure was made by the State Commissioner for Environment and Housing, Hamisu Muazu Shira, while briefing Newsmen at the commencement of the exercise held at the main entrance of the Government House, Bauchi, on Friday. The Commissioner explained that the 5-day spraying exercise was designed to be conducted in strategic locations within the Bauchi metropolis and other major towns across the state saying that: ” We are basically here today to begin the spread against the COVID-19, the state government has supported us to conduct this exercise.” Hamisu Shira added that:” His Excellency, Senator Bala Mohammed, has assured of his support in this exercise so as to keep the citizens from this deadly virus,” adding that the exercise will be extended to other parts of the state as part of government’s efforts to tackle the spread of coronavirus in the state. The Commissioner also said that over 300 personnel are to partake in the exercise, calling on stakeholders in the state to support the exercise in to ensure its success.  YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE Buy and read digital replicas of your TRIBUNE titles by subscribing through E-VENDING Nigeria, Chad, Niger Commence Joint Onslaught Against Boko Haram Poised to quell the lingering insurgency, nations around the Lake Chad basin, Nigeria, Chad and Niger have commenced a joint “massive” onslaught against Boko Haram. According to the Voice of America, tweeting at voanews.com, the joint offensive is a renewed operation following the inadequacies of the multinational force of countries… Read full story We Will Defeat COVID-19, But I Don’t Want Any Casualty —Makinde The governor of Oyo State, Engineer Seyi Makinde, on Monday, tested positive to Coronavirus otherwise known as Covid-19. In this interview monitored on the Broadcasting Corporation o